1d8QX7AklB8.title: #Sai96 | 96th Advent of Love; Evening Program
1d8QX7AklB8.description:
As we celebrate the 96th Advent of the Avatar of Pure Love, may we love You so much, that every act of ours is a reflection Your message, every thought - a ray of Your compassion, and every work soaked with the sweetness of Your love. ❤️🙏🏽


"I have no desire to celebrate such birthdays. As I was coming, I was greeted by many wishing me "Happy Birthday". I am always happy. Why should anyone wish me "Happy Birthday"? Be happy yourselves. Your happiness is my Happiness. I don't expect anything from you. Just develop love within you. Regard all mankind with fraternal feelings. Recognize all as the children of God. Bear no ill will or hatred toward anyone. Don't hurt anyone's feelings. Only such a large-hearted attitude will confer on you limitless bliss. If you are celebrating Swami's birthday, this is all that I desire from you. Have unity among yourselves. Strive to revive and promote the glory of India (Bharath)." - Divine Discourse [65th Birthday]: 23 November 1990.

h4UWyijSYm0.title: #Sai96 | Feature Film Presentation: Unity is Divinity
h4UWyijSYm0.description:
This broadcast is protected by Canadian copyright law. Reproduction and distribution in any form without the prior, written permission of the Sri Sathya Sai Baba Centre of Toronto-York is prohibited. Copyright 2021 Sri Sathya Sai Baba Centre of Toronto-York. All Rights Reserved.

On behalf of the Sri Sathya Sai Baba Centre of Toronto - York, welcome to the feature presentation for our #Sai96 offerings!

This morning we have the opportunity to watch our centre's first-ever feature film presentation titled: "Unity is Divinity", starring the Group 3 and 4 SSE students! This presentation is unlike any other offering before, as all students were filmed independently, adhering to COVID-19 protocols, whilst still maintaining an intriguing storyline with valuable life lessons.

Be sure to tune in to all our centre celebration offerings for the 96th Year of the Advent of our beloved Bhagawan Sri Sathya Sai Baba.

Friday November 19th:
Group 1 & Group 2 Girls SSE Presentations @ 7:00pm-8:00pm

Saturday November 20th:
Group 2 Boys & Group 3 Girls Presentation Offerings @ 7:00pm-8:00pm

Sunday November 21nd:
Pre-SSE Offering @ 10:00am - 12:00pm
Group 3 & 4 Feature Presentation: @ 10:00am- 11:00am

Tuesday November 23rd:
Morning Program @ 6:00am-9:00am
Evening Program @ 7:00pm-9:00pm

As we celebrate the 96th Year of the Advent of our beloved Bhagawan, let us all continue to be united through prayer.

VACQrl7kz4s.description:
Evening Program:

Vedam
Ashtotharam
Sathya to Sai: Ep. 12- Manasa Bhajare Guru Charanam
Bhajans
Swami's Discourse, Aarti

To celebrate this landmark event in Baba’s life - 20th October every year is celebrated as the Avatar Declaration Day. It is on this historically significant day in the year 1940 that the young lad Sathyanarayana Raju revealed to the world His Divine identity and the glorious mission on which He has come.

yijA5s-JX1c.title: Unity is Divinity Talk Series Part 5 : "Religions are Many; God is One" with Aravind Balasubramanya
yijA5s-JX1c.description:
Om Sri Sai Ram,

Please join us for Part 5 of our Unity is Divinity Talk Series, as part of the Building Extension and Stupa Project spiritual offering.

This week's guest speaker is Brother Aravind Balasubramanya, and the talk is entitled "Religions are Many; God is One". 

Aravind Balasubramanya is an alumnus of Sri Sathya Sai Institute of Higher Learning and is an avid photographer and is an author. Through his blogs and YouTube videos, he continually inspires devotees to feel connected to Swami. 

Please tune in live via www.sathyasaitoronto.org/live.
Brother Arvind's YouTube Channel: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCUqq3YFvli01AzGHu8Ixr5g

9sEKBPwsziI.title: Special Program | Ganesh Chaturthi, Sept 10, 2021
9sEKBPwsziI.description:
Special Program | Ganesh Chaturthi, Sept 10, 2021

Today's Schedule:
8:00 PM | Vedam
8:15 PM | Special Ganesh Chaturthi Offering
9:15 PM | Aarti & Meditation

Another name for Vinayaka is ‘Vighneswara’. Easwara is one who is endowed with every conceivable form of wealth: riches, knowledge, health, bliss, beauty, etc. Vighneswara is the promoter of all these forms of wealth and removes all obstacles to their enjoyment. He confers all these forms of wealth on those who worship Him.

Let us forget all our worries, anxieties, and do constant contemplation on Lord Ganesha, the remover of obstacles. Let us derive bliss out of singing these songs and bhajans.

_H02dJGngug.title: Special Program | Krishna Janamashtami, Evening Program
_H02dJGngug.description:
The Sri Sathya Sai Baba Centre of Toronto - York cordially invites all to the festive Krishna Janmashtami Celebrations to be broadcast through our website (sathyasaitoronto.org/live).

Whatever you do, remember the Omnipresence of the Divine. Do every act to please God, out of love and not out of compulsion. Divinise every act. The Lord declares in the Gita, "Having been born in this transient and unhappy world, worship Me."

Krishna called upon Arjuna to stand up and face the battle, reminding him of what was in store for the evil minded Kauravas. He adjured Arjuna to have full faith in Him and do his duty. Then Arjuna declared, "I shall do as You bid me (Karishyevachanam thava)." Then Krishna declared, "You have now become My true devotee." And He exhorted Arjuna to rise and fight the battle, which would end in the complete destruction of the Kauravas and the wicked quartet, Duryodhana, Dussaasana, Karna, and Sakuni.

The great teaching of the Gita is this: Put your trust in God, carry on your duties, be helpful to everyone, and sanctify your lives. Dedicate all actions to God. That is the way to experience oneness with God. God is in you. You are in God. This oneness is the basic truth. Chant the name of the Lord and render social service in a spirit of selflessness and devotion to God.

Divine Discourse: Sri Krishna Janmashtami, 18 August 1995

Stay connected to our weekly devotional activities with our virtual broadcasts! Join us every Sunday from 10:00am until 12:15pm!

Let us all continue to be united through prayer - by singing bhajans and chanting the Gayathri Mantra with intensity as much as possible. This is an important spiritual practice that can alleviate this global health threat.

Feel free to share the stream with all your family and friends.

VxZweQcGBOU.title: Unity is Divinity Talk Series Part 4 : "E pluribus unum, Out of many, one" with Janani Srinivasan
VxZweQcGBOU.description:
Om Sri Sai Ram,

Please join us for Part 4 of our Unity is Divinity Talk Series, as part of the Building Extension and Stupa Project spiritual offering.

This week's guest speaker is Sister Janani Srinivasan, and the talk is entitled "E pluribus unum, Out of many, one". 

Even before Janani was as born, Swami made sure he had established himself firmly in the hearts and lives of her family. Her father, Prof. Srinivasan, was appointed by Swami as Professor and Head of the Physics department of the Sathya Sai University and served there from 1983 to 2002. She and her family have received (and continue to receive) innumerable blessings from Bhagawan over the course of their association with Him. Janani studied in the Sri Sathya Sai Higher Secondary School in Puttaparthi from Grade 1 to 12. Post Parthi, she holds a B.sc and an MBA from the Rotman School of Management, Toronto. She used to work for a major Canadian bank. She currently lives with her husband in Princeton, NJ.

Please tune in live via www.sathyasaitoronto.org/live.

6753wOHB5yY.title: Guru Poornima 2021 | Evening Program
6753wOHB5yY.description:
Evening Program:
7:00 pm: Omkar & Vedam 
7:15 pm: Special Tribute to SSE Gurus
7:20 pm: SSE Connect Short Film
7:25 pm: Young Adult Musical Offering
7:50 pm: Special Satsang
8:50 pm: Swami’s Discourse and Bhajan
9:00 pm: Aarthi & Closing Prayers

All programs are available at sathyasaitoronto.org/live

On July 24, 2021, Guru Poornima Day, we express our gratitude and love to our Guru and God, Bhagawan Sri Sathya Sai Baba.

Through this offering at the Divine Lotus Feet of our beloved Guru, for Guru Poornima 2021, we pray that it helps us cultivate an ever-deeper connection with God. As Bhagawan said in his Guru Poornima discourse on 22 July 1994, "the Lord confers full grace on those whose hearts are totally filled with devotion and realize the divine." As we commemorate yet another Guru Poornima celebration let us pray for His grace, because it is only through HIM and HIS grace that we can dispel the darkness of ignorance and attain Self-Realization.

5o1Wd0d0N7k.title: Special Prayers | Unity is Divinity
5o1Wd0d0N7k.description:
Om Sri Sai Ram,

Sathya Sai Baba assures us that Unity is Divinity.  As a loving Centre we must remain united in our love for Swami and remind ourselves that there is no greater power than the power of prayer.  

Throughout this process, our focus is in maintaining vibrant programs for our membership family and ensuring the long-term well-being of our Centre. At this time, we share the feeling that faith, devotion, and patience are of utmost importance for all of us as more information comes available each week.

With this conviction, we are inviting you and your family to join in a special prayerful satsang tonight to seek Swami's blessing and guidance.

d1xwdY4T_7Q.title: Special Talk by Dr. Sunder Iyer | What Does it Mean to be a Sai Student: Living the Sai Way
d1xwdY4T_7Q.description:
Sai Ram,
Please join us this Sunday, July 11 at 12:45pm for a special talk by Dr. Sunder Iyer.

Dr. Sunder Iyer has been practicing the science of Yoga since the age of 10. During his youth, Dr. Iyer spent over 15 years at the ashram of Sri Sathya Sai Baba. In the early 1980s, Dr. Iyer spent 2 years serving as Swami’s personal household attendant. In this special talk (originally presented to SSE Students on May 16, 2021), Dr. Iyer shares his knowledge of human advancement to help others experience life to its fullest potential. 

Feel free to share the stream with all your family and friends.

sathyasaitoronto.org/live

X6rt5vze2SU.title: Unity is Divinity Talk Series Part 3 |  Saturday June 5, 2021
X6rt5vze2SU.description:
Sai Ram, Please join us on Saturday June 5th, at 10:00 am for Part 3 of our Unity is Divinity Talk Series, as part of the Building Extension and Stupa Project spiritual offering.

This week's guest speaker is Brother Imindu Liyanage, and the talk is entitled "Finding the Unity in Divinity: A Case Study of a Buddhist Sai Devotee". Against the prevailing nontheistic tides of Buddhism, how does this (especially flawed) Sai Devotee find his way to the reality of divinity?

Brother Imindu serves as an SSE Guru and Education Coordinator at the Sri Sathya Sai Baba Centre of Victoria Park. Among his other work, he researches the inflammation and management of COVID-19 and studies Medicine at the University of Toronto.

w6XYJD_mizM.title: Unity is Divinity Talk Series Part 2: SSE Presentation | Sunday May 9, 2021
w6XYJD_mizM.description:
Sai Ram, join us for Part 2 of the 5-Part 'Unity is Divinity Talk Series', as part of the Building Extension and Stupa project from 9:55 am to 10:45 am. 

For this year’s Parent Day Celebration, the Group 4 SSE Students have put together an offering in conjunction with the Centre’s BEST project. Over the past few months, the children have spent time understanding what the Stupa symbolizes and, in the process, have reflected on what Swami says about dharma, religion, and what it is we should focus on. This multimedia offer has been conceptualizing prepared with lots of love by the Group 4 children. The aim of this offering to provide us all with a deeper understanding of a message that it’s often shared but perhaps not reflected on as often.

IIPH8PAJAF8.title: Special Program | Ram Navami, April 18, 2021
IIPH8PAJAF8.description:
Special Program | Ram Navami, Apr 18, 2021

Today's Schedule:
10:00AM - Divine Discourse of Bhagavan Sri Sathya Sai Baba
11:00AM - Vedam
11:15AM - Bhajans
12:00PM - Aarthi
12:10PM - Sai Gayathri (9 times)
The program concludes at 12:15PM

This day, the birth of Sri Rama is celebrated in all lands. Rama had deed, word and thought, body, speech and mind, ever pure and totally free from blemish. Really speaking, one ought to revere the story of Rama as a profound allegory. Every act and actor in that story attracts attention and gets imprinted on the memory because the allegory is personal to each of us.

It is often said that Rama followed dharma at all times. This is not the correct way of describing him. He did not follow dharma, he was dharma. What he thought, spoke, and did was dharma and is dharma forever.
- Divine Discourse April 18, 1986

eWGl4FNtbyA.title: 21 Gayathri Mantra Chanting- Daily Sadhana
eWGl4FNtbyA.description:
Om Bhur Bhuvaḥ Swaḥ
Tat-savitur Vareñyaṃ
Bhargo Devasya Dheemahi
Dhiyo Yonaḥ Prachodayāt

We meditate on that most adored Supreme Lord, the creator, whose effulgence (divine light) illumines all realms (physical, mental and spiritual). May this divine light illumine our intellect.

Let us all continue to be united through prayer - by singing bhajans and chanting the Gayathri Mantra with intensity as much as possible. This is an important spiritual practice that can alleviate this global health threat.

U_Ifps7BaOQ.title: Guided Jyoti Meditation
U_Ifps7BaOQ.description:
"Since the light illumines all the senses every day so deeply and so systematically, a time will soon come when you can no more relish dark and evil sights, yearn for dark and sinister tales, crave for base, harmful, deadening toxic food and drink, handle dirty demeaning things, approach places of ill-fame and injury, or frame evil designs against anyone at any time. Stay on in that thrill of witnessing the light everywhere. If you are adoring God in any form now, try to visualize that form in the all-pervasive light. For Light is God; God is Light.

"Practice this meditation as I have advised regularly every day. At other times repeat the name of God (any Name fragrant with any of His many Majesties), always taking care to be conscious of His might, mercy, and munificence."

- Sri Sathya Sai Baba
Sathya Sai Speaks, Volume X, Page 348-350, Shivarathri, 1979

GhiDOGyyhKs.title: Special Program | Presidential Inauguration & Bhajans
GhiDOGyyhKs.description:
Join us for the Inauguration and Oath Taking Ceremony of Brother Sudhakar Voora, incoming President of the Sri Sathya Sai Baba Centre of Toronto-York for the 2021-2022 term.

The virtual ceremony will include an announcement of the incoming members of the Executive Team, and the Office Bearers Oath ceremony.

The program will be followed by a Special Satsang and arathi, from 11:15 am to 12:30 pm, with a live video feed from the Prayer Hall in the Centre. We thank Swami for giving us the opportunity to safely connect us back to the altar, hall, and home we all love and miss so dearly.

Please do reach out to Brother Sudhakar and the entire incoming team to show your support as they embark on this journey of love, bringing opportunities for us all to grow spiritually, and eventually come back together in our Home at 40 Voyager Court North.

Please join us tonight as we ring in 2021 with lots of love, positive energy and prayers! Tonight’s program begins with "Year in Review" presentation starting at 10:00pm followed by Special Satsang to midnight. 

The Satsang will be followed by the announcement of our next Centre President for 2021-2022. Let us come together with our families and extend all of our support to our next President and the whole incoming team for a successful term!

Tonights program includes:
2020 | Year in Review
Likitha Japam | 108 Times
Vedam
Sri Sathya Sai Ashtotharam
Swami’s Discourse
Special Bhajans
Swami Sings
Special Announcement | Dr. Peter Hacker
Closing Remarks & Farewell | President Amar Lad

xc9cSw3z1CM.title: Christmas Day | Devotional Program
xc9cSw3z1CM.description:
Special Program | Christmas in Parthi

'Develop love of God. All other forms of love are not love at all but only fleeting and impermanent attachments. Man's biggest folly is forgetting his Divinity. All should realize that they come from God. All are children of God. Everyone should seek to get nearer and nearer to God. That is spiritual practice (sadana). You must feel that God dwells in your heart ( hridayavasi). You must develop compassion in the heart, because without it, the heart is only a stone.

That is the message of Jesus: The message of love. Love is God. Live in love. Start the day with love. Spend the day with love. End the day with love. This is the way to God. Only the person who is filled with love will be dear to the Lord.'
- Divine Discourse: 25 December 1996

Join us this festive morning as we relive the beautiful Christmas program offered on Christmas morning in Prashanti Nilayam. Original date of program - December 25th, 2014 & December 27th, 2014. 

sathyasaitoronto.org/live

ug8j27D6cmI.title: #Sai95 | Talk by Dr. Srinivas Raghavan
ug8j27D6cmI.description:
Continuing on with the celebrations of the 95th Advent of Pure Love, SSIO Canada Education Wing brings you a special talk by none other than Dr. Srinivas Raghavan entitled "Sai Spiritual Education, a transformation for gurus, parents, and children."

Br. Srinivas will be taking questions, please feel free to drop any questions you may have in the comments box. we will try our best to get address as many as we can.

Srinivas is very blessed in being Sai’s instrument. He has composed many devotional songs such as, ‘Remind me my Lord’, ‘Chant the name of God’, ‘Sai you are my heart and soul’ and ‘Sai mere darasa dikhao’, some of which are sung in various Sai centres. In his presentation he will be sharing Sai’s message of love through personal experiences and devotional songs. Srinivas received his MS & PhD degrees in Computer Science (Ohio State University) specialising in the study of Human Computer Experience. He also received an MBA degree (Rady School of Business) specialising in Innovation Management. Presently he heads his own consulting firm, iYOUSE Inc., working with leading companies in wireless technology, healthcare and education.

As we celebrate the 95th Advent of the Avatar of Pure Love, may we love You so much, that every act of ours is a reflection Your message, every thought - a ray of Your compassion, and every work soaked with the sweetness of Your love. ❤️🙏🏽

Join & follow us on all our socials:
sathyasaitoronto.org/live
https://www.facebook.com/torontoyorksai/
https://mixlr.com/torontoyorksai
https://www.instagram.com/torontoyorksai

"I have no desire to celebrate such birthdays. As I was coming, I was greeted by many wishing me "Happy Birthday". I am always happy. Why should anyone wish me "Happy Birthday"? Be happy yourselves. Your happiness is my Happiness. I don't expect anything from you. Just develop love within you. Regard all mankind with fraternal feelings. Recognize all as the children of God. Bear no ill will or hatred toward anyone. Don't hurt anyone's feelings. Only such a large-hearted attitude will confer on you limitless bliss. If you are celebrating Swami's birthday, this is all that I desire from you. Have unity among yourselves. Strive to revive and promote the glory of India (Bharath)." - Divine Discourse [65th Birthday]: 23 November 1990.

"I have no desire to celebrate such birthdays. As I was coming, I was greeted by many wishing me "Happy Birthday". I am always happy. Why should anyone wish me "Happy Birthday"? Be happy yourselves. Your happiness is my Happiness. I don't expect anything from you. Just develop love within you. Regard all mankind with fraternal feelings. Recognize all as the children of God. Bear no ill will or hatred toward anyone. Don't hurt anyone's feelings. Only such a large-hearted attitude will confer on you limitless bliss. If you are celebrating Swami's birthday, this is all that I desire from you. Have unity among yourselves. Strive to revive and promote the glory of India (Bharath)." - Divine Discourse [65th Birthday]: 23 November 1990.

05r0uG4xFmE.title: Global Akhanda Bhajans | Virtual Offering
05r0uG4xFmE.description:
This is a unique Global Akhanda Bhajan offering at Bhagawan's lotus feet this year. As all may not be able to travel to the Centre at this time, here is an opportunity to participate in this sacred event from wherever one is.

Let’s come together virtually, sing His glory, fill our hearts with His love, and spread the sacred vibes of His divine name!

"Today we are having the Akhanda Bhajan (nonstop global bhajan by Sai devotees all over the world). This is being done not for the sake of one individual, one nation or one community. It is for the welfare of humanity as a whole. 

The bhajans that are sung permeate the ether in the form of sound waves and fill the entire atmosphere. Thereby the whole environment gets purified. Breathing in this purified atmosphere, our hearts get purified. Reciting the Lord's name is a process of give and take. Singing the Lord's name should become an exercise in mutual sharing of joy and holiness. It should be remembered that the sounds we produce reverberate in the atmosphere. They remain permanently in the ether as waves and outlast the individual uttering the sounds."
- Sathya Sai Baba, Divine Discourse, November 8, 1986

11:00am | Special Ganesh Chaturthi Offering
12:00pm | Aarti & Meditation

Another name for Vinayaka is ‘Vighneswara’. Easwara is one who is endowed with every conceivable form of wealth: riches, knowledge, health, bliss, beauty, etc. Vighneswara is the promoter of all these forms of wealth and removes all obstacles to their enjoyment. He confers all these forms of wealth on those who worship Him.

Let us forget all our worries, anxieties, and do constant contemplation on Lord Ganesha, the remover of obstacles. Let us derive bliss out of singing these songs and bhajans.

BDsuPDQt1_0.title: Special Program | Krishna Janamashtami, Aug 12, 2020
BDsuPDQt1_0.description:
Special Program | Krishna Janamashtami, Aug 12, 2020

Today's Schedule:
8:00pm | Special Krishna Janamashtami Offering
8:25pm | Bhajans
9:10pm | Divine Discourse
9:15pm | Aarti & Meditation

God incarnated as Krishna to charm humanity by His pranks, His play, His song and sweetness, and to show man the path of love and how to live in love. Krishna was born on ashtami (eighth day) during the dark fortnight of the month. The effulgence of the Lord is seen with greater effect when it is dark. In a world of disorder, Krishna was born to establish order. Ashtami is associated with troubles and difficulties. When do troubles arise? When righteousness is forgotten. Krishna's advent signifies the dispelling of darkness, the removal of troubles, the banishing of ignorance and the teaching of mankind of the supreme wisdom.

qaUzLhsfrz4.title: Guru Purnima | Day Program
qaUzLhsfrz4.description:
"Manasa Bhajare Guru Charanam, Dustara Bhavasagara Taranam - I called on all those suffering in the endless round of birth and death to worship the Feet of the Guru (spiritual preceptor), the Guru who was announcing Himself, who had come again for taking upon Himself the burden of those who find refuge in Him. That was the very first Message of Mine to Humanity. Manasa bhajare — Worship in the mind!" - Sathya Sai Speaks vol 1; Ch 1. October 1953

On the auspicious day of Guru Poornima, the Sri Sathya Sai Baba Centre of Toronto-York cordially invites all devotees to join for a full-day online program aimed to re-connect us to the divine teaching of our dear Guru, Sathya Sai Baba. The program is broken down into four parts and strives to tie together the lessons from our month-long study of the Prema Vahini, Swami's first written Vahini. 

Day Program:
Welcome
Feature Talk | Br. Sanjay Mahalingam
Break
Feature Talk & Q&A | Mani Bashyam
Swami's Discourse
Aarti & Closing

localized.title: Guru Purnima | Morning Program
localized.description:
"Manasa Bhajare Guru Charanam, Dustara Bhavasagara Taranam - I called on all those suffering in the endless round of birth and death to worship the Feet of the Guru (spiritual preceptor), the Guru who was announcing Himself, who had come again for taking upon Himself the burden of those who find refuge in Him. That was the very first Message of Mine to Humanity. Manasa bhajare — Worship in the mind!" - Sathya Sai Speaks vol 1; Ch 1. October 1953

On the auspicious day of Guru Poornima, the Sri Sathya Sai Baba Centre of Toronto-York cordially invites all devotees to join for a full-day online program aimed to re-connect us to the divine teaching of our dear Guru, Sathya Sai Baba. The program is broken down into four parts and strives to tie together the lessons from our month-long study of the Prema Vahini, Swami's first written Vahini. 

Morning Program:
Omkara & Suprabhatam
Veda Chanting
Sathya Sai Ashrotharam (108 Names)
Swami's Discourse
Bhajans & Aarti

mqoUPvl5BXU.title: Special Broadcast | Bhajan Sandhya, 1999
mqoUPvl5BXU.description:
The Sri Sathya Sai Baba Centre of Toronto-York hosted their 13th annual Bhajan Sandhya on Saturday May 8th, 1999. The evening of inspirational music was geared to arouse the awareness of inherent divinity and peace. Our sincere thanks to the singers and musicians who participated in the program.

Dr. Anand Bala
A devotee of Bhagawan Sri Sathya Sai Baba, hails from a family of Indian Classical musicians, spanning six generations. He has maintained his rich music heritage by delighting and inspiring audiences across Canada. 

Sathya Vishwanathan
An alumni of the Sri Sathya Sai Institute of Higher Learning, developed great interest in tabla in the divine presence of Bhagawan and through self-mastery became a tabla player par-excellence. 

Youth Girls
Mona Patel, Hema Morarji, and Agila Allalasundaram, are all university and college students. They are blessed to be born and raised into families dedicated to Bhagawan Sri Sathya Sai Baba. They have melodious voices and each a unique style of their own. Love for the Lord is constantly felt in their renditions.

Youth Group
Comprised of a group of our talented and devotional youth girls inspired the audience with their enchanting voices. 

“Chanting the name of the Lord, the practice of Namasmarana, is acceptable to all religions. It brings about the unity of all. Namasmarana is a way to purify the air. But, by singing or saying the Name of the Lord, You can become purified.” - Sathya Sai Baba

hMqJ2BF4jy4.title: Bhajan Sandhya for Peace | 1998
hMqJ2BF4jy4.description:
The Sri Sathya Sai Baba Centre of Toronto-York hosted their 12th annual Bhajan Sandhya on Saturday May 30th, 1998. The theme of the program was peace in the world and a fervent prayer "It starts with me." The evening of inspirational music was geared to arouse the awareness of inherent divinity and peace. Our sincere thanks to the singers and musicians who participated in the program.

The program includes offerings by the youth girls of the Sai Spiritual Education program, and 15 year old Aneela Maharaj, a student of Purabi Banerjee.

Rupak Changkakoti, Ph.D
Rupak is a graduate of the Sri Sathya Sai Institute of Higher Learning in Puttaparthi where he was fortunate to spend thirteen years at the Lotus Feet of Bhagawan. The voice that has captivated and inspired thousands is a blessing and a gift from Swami. He has produced the album "Sai Katha" the life story of Sathya Sai Baba. Rupak is accompanied by Amit Ray Surva, a gifted musician on the harmonium, Sanjay Verma, a versatile tablist, and Shamin Arefin, a keen musician from Bangladesh. 

Behroze Chatterjee
A graduate of arts from Nagpur University, India, she is a versatile artiste who excels in singing ghazals, bhajans, hindi film songs and folk songs in the regional languages of India. Behroze was bestowed the Shiromani Award in 1992 for her contribution in the field of singing towards national integration. Behroze is accompanied on the tabla by Amit Kumar, a versatile tabla player, Sharma Ramdular, a talented keyboard player, and Jatin Gujrati on percussion.

VxHln7Fe9Tk.title: Special Talk | Rev. Dr. Bhante Saranapala
VxHln7Fe9Tk.description:
On April 29th, 2018 on the occasion of Vesak - Buddha Purnima, the centre was delighted to welcome Rev. Dr. Bhante Saranapala who gave a very enlightening study circle on the significance of Buddha Purnima and Mindful Meditation. He says, “To be mindful is to be kind to yourself and others".

Dr. Bhante Saranapala is renowned as the “Urban Buddhist Monk,” an appropriate moniker for a Buddhist monk for modern times. He is acclaimed as a consummate teacher of meditation by a growing number of seekers of the Buddhist way of life in North America and Europe who admire his simple and all-embracing approach in transmitting the universal message of love, understanding and compassion of Buddha. 

He has earned an enviable reputation as a preacher and a meditation master par excellence. After obtaining a master’s degree in religious studies from Hamilton’s McMaster University in 2002, Bhante returned to the University of Toronto as a teaching assistant, and did his doctoral studies in Religious Studies at the Centre for the Study of Religion. He is the founder of Canada: A Mindful and Kind Nation and in 2017, the Government of Canada presented him with the Canadian Charter of Rights and Freedoms.

"Meditation is a healing technique, it is inner work, it is not just sitting and breathing. There is more to be done and this is what most people do not know about meditation. This is beyond mindfulness. We meditate often because we want inner-peace but our inner problems do not disappear immediately. You have to do the inner work. Meditation is all about looking within."

"It is the foremost duty of children to fulfil the wishes of their mother and make her happy. Serve others to the extent possible. You need not take up any service activity beyond your means and capacity. If you find your neigh- bours suffering, give them solace. Help them to the extent possible and make them happy. This is what I expect you to learn today. On the occasion of Easwaramma Day, I exhort all of you to practise these three principles of service, experience bliss, and share it with all." - Divine Discourse, May 6th 2006.

iYpDavQpWH8.title: Eashwaramma Day Special | "We are His Legacy"
iYpDavQpWH8.description:
The celebration of the life of Mother Eashwaramma, the mother of Sathya Sai Baba, began on May 6, 1977 as Children’s Day in commemoration of her death anniversary. Sathya Sai Baba has said innumerable times that the mother is man’s first preceptor (Guru). Mother Eashwaramma is the example of an ideal mother. On May 6, Eashwaramma’s life is celebrated around the world by remembering her exemplary life, performing acts of selfless service for the needy, and singing the glories of God.

The SSE children presented this offering of gratitude on Easwaramma Day (May 2017). The offering was taken up as a Sadhana to be offered at the lotus feet of Swami. Over the past few months, the children have - on their own - planned, prepared and executed this offering. The theme "We are His Legacy" was chosen by the children. The offering has multiple components in the interest of including as many children as possible in various ways. The presentation consists of speech, songs, and an audio-visual component. A very unique component of this project was that the children took upon themselves a 20 week personal sadhana, which became a contract between them and Swami, and offered at His divine lotus feet.

XImkixwCdx4.title: Special Program | Buddha Purnima, May 7th.
XImkixwCdx4.description:
Today's Program:
8:00pm | Special Buddha Purnima Bhajans
9:00pm | Gayathri Chanting (108 Times)
9:40pm | Aarti & Meditation

In a discourse on February 12, 1989, Baba said, “There are two categories of happiness in the world: Acquired Happiness and Self-generating Bliss. Acquired happiness is associated with sensory objects; it arises and vanishes according to circumstances. This applies to everyone in the world; what is experienced when things are enjoyed is evanescent. So this type of joy has been described as Acquired or Derived Happiness. As it is got and lost by human effort, it is not true bliss. 

“Man, however, seeks lasting bliss (Ananda). In truth he is the embodiment of bliss and is filled with bliss. Bliss constitutes his very nature and being. It exists of itself in him, so why does he not experience it? Being unaware of his true nature, he is obsessed with the external world and fails to experience the bliss within him.”

Elaborating on this on February 1, 2001, Baba said:

“Bliss is within you; it emanates from your sacred feelings. So you have to manifest bliss from within; it cannot be bestowed on you by others. No one can take the bliss away from you, and you cannot obtain it from outside.

"With purity of heart, steadiness of mind and selfless actions, one can earn divine grace which can remove any amount of suffering in a trice. Without divine grace, one cannot achieve anything, therefore one must undertake activities that will earn that grace. Peace and happiness cannot be obtained from the external world. Only divine grace can bring you true happiness.”

Time and again through so many of His incarnations, Baba is reminding us of the same principle - All happiness is within and not without. All that is within is eternal while all that is without is ephemeral.

InzqxUM0qdw.title: Special Program | Eashwaramma Day Celebrations, May 6th.
InzqxUM0qdw.description:
04:34 Song | Gaiye Ganapati
11:16 Song | Janam Diya Tune Sai Ko
18:10 Eashwaramba Priya Tanaya
23:07 Jaya Maa, Jaya Maa, Jagadishwari Sai Maa
29:56 Parthishwari, Jagatjanani
36:02 Amba Vandanam, Eashwaramba Vandanam
42:52 Jaya Maa, Jaya Maa, Dayakaro Sai Maa
48:00 Eashwaramba Priyanandana
51:41 Swami's Discourse
56:59 Swami's Bhajan | Hari Bhajana Bina
59:04 Swami's Gayathri & Aarti

“I resolved on My Advent, decided who should be My mother. Mere humans can only choose the one who is to be the husband or wife. But the Mother was chosen by the son in the Rama and Krishna incarnations and then too, as now, the task for which the Divine Advent was decided upon was the same – the conferring of Prema on all and, through the fostering of Prema, the cultivation of righteous living among mankind.” 

The celebration of the life of Mother Eashwaramma, the mother of Sathya Sai Baba, began on May 6, 1977 as Children’s Day in commemoration of her death anniversary. Sathya Sai Baba has said innumerable times that the mother is man’s first preceptor (Guru). Mother Eashwaramma is the example of an ideal mother. On May 6, Eashwaramma’s life is celebrated around the world by remembering her exemplary life, performing acts of selfless service for the needy, and singing the glories of God.

Janam Diya, Tune Sai Ko, Humpe Kiya Upkaar. Eashwaramma, Tera Sai - Yug Yug Ka, Avatar.

Oh Eashwaramma, you have blessed the entire world by giving birth to our beloved Lord Sai. Oh Eashwaramma, your Sai is the incarnation of this age.

Join us in celebration of Mother Eashwaramma tonight. 🙏🏽❤️

DfZGKDMaDMM.title: Feature Presentation | "Dashavatara"
DfZGKDMaDMM.description:
Relive the 1998 play presented to Swami by the SSE children and young adults of the Sri Sathya Sai Baba Centre of Toronto - York. 

Lord Vishnu is the preserver of the universe. In order to restore cosmic order, he descended on earth in ten different forms, or, "Dashavatara". In each of his lifetimes, he eradicated evil and revived dharma. This play, entitled "Dashavatara" brings to life the 10 incarnations of Lord Vishnu.

EHphg_7QZZ0.title: Gems of Devotion | An Offering of Gratitude (1984)
EHphg_7QZZ0.description:
We are pleased to release these "Gems of Devotion" in honour of Sri Sathya Sai Aradhana Mahotsavam. 

Gems of Devotion | Vol. 5
01:06 | Ganapathi Deva
08:45 | Sairam Sairam
11:31 | Hey Ghanashyam Muralidhara
15:55 | Pashupathey Shiva Shankara
20:00 | Sai Chitravathi Tat Vasini
24:25 | Nitham Smaranam Sai Bhavam
28:12 | Sri Sathya Sai Maam Pahi
33:19 | Tumho Mere Praan Baba
38:21 | Jaganmatha Hey Sai Maa
41:58 | Sai Govinda Krishna Janardhana
46:57 | Sai Mata Tumho Amba Bhavani
50:35 | Smarana Nandam

Pulled from our archived, these 12 petals of love were composed by members of the Sri Sathya Sai Baba Centre of Toronto-York and offered to Bhagawan in 1984 on the occasion of His 59th birthday.

mJBdeJfdlJI.title: Sri Sathya Sai Aradhana Mahotsavam | Evening Program
mJBdeJfdlJI.description:
On the auspicious day of Sri Sathya Sai Aradhana Mahotsavam, devotees all over the world lovingly offer their prayers by way of practicing Sathya Sai Baba’s teachings.

Evening Program Schedule:
00:05:45 | Vedam
00:15:51 | Sri Sathya Sai Ashtotharam

Special Bhajans
00:25:52 | Pahi Gajanana Deenavana
00:31:03 | Charana Kamala Vando
00:35:55 | Tumho Anatha Natha Bhagawan
00:40:04 | Antaryami Tuhi Aalola Tulsi Dhari
00:45:14 | Madhura Madhura Sai Naama
00:49:17 | Deena Bandhava Baba
00:53:29 | Anthar Jyothi Jalaao Sai
00:57:35 | Listen Listen Listen
01:01:00 | My Lord Sai
01:06:10 | Sarva Dharma Priya Deva
01:09:23 | Vel Muruga
01:14:17 | Alakh Niranjana
01:16:59 | Sai Nama Bolo
01:21:19 | Vanamali Vasudeva
01:24:18 | Eshwaramba Priyanandana
01:28:41 | Sathya Sai Padambhujam
01:31:56 | Bolo Jai Sairam

01:36:18 | Hari Bhajana Bina [Swami Sings]
01:39:00 | Swami's Discourse 
01:45:59 | Prema Muditha [Swami Sings]

01:50:09 | Madhura Mohana Ghanashyama
01:57:04 | Tu Pyaar Ka Sagar Hai

02:02:12 | Aarti & Sai Gayathri Chanting

On this auspicious day let us rededicate our lives to love Him with all our heart, soul and consciousness. Let us always remember, especially during these tough times, that Bhagawan is our Guru, God and Saviour. In His first bhajan, “Manasa Bhajaree Guru Charanam Dustara Bhava Saagara Taranam” Bhagawan assured us that, He will take us across the ocean of samsara, if we hold on to His lotus feet. He will always protect us.

The Centre will be commemorating Aradhana Mahotsavam 2020 with this Special Virtual Offering.

DyQOGUFzp1I.description:

1:00pm: Special Broadcast | Special Talk by Dr. Sunam Gyamtso

On the occasion of Shirdi Sai Jayanti on Saturday, September 28th, we were extremely blessed and grateful to have a distinguished Guest Speaker - Dr. Sunam Gyamtso Tenzin join us for a divine satsang. 

Date: Saturday Sept 28, 2019.
Location: Sri Sathya Sai Baba Centre of Toronto-York

---

Dr. Sunam has been blessed with many Divine interactions with Bhagavan Baba from childhood, having been called into his physical fold in the 1970s. He was a student of Sri Sathya Sai Institutions from high school through his doctoral studies. He is a wonderful speaker and a versatile musician with talents in singing, composing, and playing on the harmonium, tabla, accordion and much more. Dr. Sunam has composed many bhajans which have become part of regular bhajan sessions at Sai Centers around the world. 

His compositions include bhajans such as: 
Jaya Shri Ganesha Vigna Naasha Gajanana 
Jaya Kailashapathe 
Sai Baba Sakala Bhuvana Ke Daata 
Raghukula Bhooshana Rajeeva Nayana 
Mata Maheshwari Tribhuvana Janani 
Araja Suno Mere Parama Kripalu 
Anupama Sundara Nanda Kishora and many many more…. 

Dr. Sunam was instrumental in composing the music for many of the plays and dramas that Bhagawan wrote and directed for the students. He currently lives in Gangtok, Sikkim, India.

Cq_2NPnucEk.title: Anil Kumar Visit, May 2019 | Toronto-York Centre
Cq_2NPnucEk.description:
Professor Anil Kumar is best known for translating Bhagawan Sri Sathya Sai Baba’s discourses to English. He was the principle of the Brindavan Campus and was a former faculty member of the Bioscience Dept. at the Sri Sathya Sai Institute of Higher Learning. Professor Anil Kumar has authored over 30 books.

On Sunday, May 19, Professor Anil Kumar gave a talk at the Sri Sathya Sai Baba Centre of Toronto-York, from 11:00 am to 1:00 pm.
